FBIS4-15568 "drsov069_a_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Communist Protesters Picket U.S. Embassy Communist Protesters Picket U.S. Embassy LD1004100994 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0930 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004100994 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] Members of the All-Union Communist Party of Bolsheviks today picketed the U.S. Embassy in Moscow. In the opinion of the pickets, the authorities in the United States, Japan, and South Korea are conducting a provocative policy toward the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. The party members believe socialist Korea is sticking in the throats of various reactionary forces in the world, and so all progressive people on the planet should show solidarity with the heroic people of North Korea.
